## 1. What this project is

IR4 is a **standalone, on-premise safety command-centre platform**: one installation, one deployment, no multi-tenancy, no `site_id`/location column anywhere. Field hardware streams data over a token-authenticated REST API; operators work in a real-time Inertia web UI plus a kiosk display. **Nothing calls the public internet** ÔÇö no CDN scripts/fonts, no analytics, no cloud SDKs. CI greps shipped code for external hosts and fails the build if found.

## 2. Stack

PHP 8.4+, Laravel 13.9+, Laravel React Starter Kit (React 19 + TypeScript + Inertia 3 + Tailwind 4 + shadcn/ui + Vite), Fortify, Reverb (self-hosted), Redis, MySQL 8+/PostgreSQL 15+, `spatie/laravel-permission`, `barryvdh/laravel-dompdf`, `endroid/qr-code`, Larastan + Pest + Pint.

## 3. Three entry surfaces ÔÇö never blur them

| Surface | Who | Transport | Routes | Auth |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **A. Operator UI** | logged-in staff | Inertia (+ session JSON helpers e.g. `/api/dashboard/summary`, `/api/equipment/by-token/ÔÇŽ`) | `routes/web.php` | Fortify session + RBAC |
| **B. Device API** | field hardware | REST JSON (`/api/ingest/*`, heartbeats) | `routes/api.php` | `auth.device` |
| **C. Public page** | LAN QR scanners | read-only page | `routes/web.php` public group | none, rate-limited |

- Operator CRUD uses Inertia forms ÔÇö not fetch/axios.
- Live screens: Inertia snapshot Ôćĺ Reverb Ôćĺ LIVE/RECONNECTING Ôćĺ poll fallback.
- Authenticated scan/summary JSON helpers are surface A, not device API.

## 4. Global data conventions

- Soft deletes on compliance/evidence/log tables. **Exception:** `audit_logs` is append-only (no `deleted_at`, never pruned; only the privileged DOC-19 wipe may remove them).
- `created_by` on human-writable tables; machine/system rows leave it null. Actor columns (`generated_by`, `published_by`, `logged_by`, ÔÇŽ) follow the same nullable-FK pattern.
- No `site_id`/tenant column ever.
- Timestamps UTC. Enums: PHP backed Ôćĺ `php artisan ir4:export-enums` Ôćĺ never hand-edit `enums.ts`.
- Controllers stay thin: FormRequest Ôćĺ policy Ôćĺ service Ôćĺ Inertia/`JsonResource`/`ApiResponse`.

## 5. Three-path data origin

| Path | Writer | `created_by` |
|---|---|---|
| ÔĹá Device | `/api/ingest/*` | NULL |
| ÔĹí System | jobs/services/scheduler | NULL |
| ÔĹó User | Inertia + FormRequest | user id |

Machine truth is immutable. Human judgment is always path ÔĹó. Alerts are path ÔĹí only. Incidents/LSR/vehicle violations are path ÔĹó only (alerts may prefill, never insert).

## 6. Module invariants (written docs)

- **Equipment (DOC-13):** `qr_token` set once at create; never regenerate. Public `/e/{token}` Ôëá authed by-token lookup.
- **HSE/LSR (DOC-14):** no service auto-insert; mandatory action fields; PPE-linked LSR keeps `worker_id` null.
- **Weekly reports (DOC-15):** freeze `data` at generation; published reports immutable; amend via superseding report; declare sensor outages (>20%).
- **Dashboard (DOC-16):** permission-filtered aggregate; dark-first Control Room tokens; `/display` stays authenticated.
- **Audit (DOC-17):** append-only; mask secrets; config/security models via `Auditable`; read-only roles get allow-listed `data_access`; no user create/update/delete of audit rows.
- **Settings (DOC-18):** whitelist only via `SettingsRegistry`; per-key permissions; sensitive keys need confirm; printer/backup paths stay `.env`.
- **Retention (DOC-19):** prune allow-list only; compliance never pruned; encrypted separate-volume backups; wipe requires verified export + confirm phrase.

## 7. RBAC ÔÇö never check role names

Four layers for every capability: route middleware Ôćĺ policy/FormRequest Ôćĺ resource field-stripping Ôćĺ frontend UX guard. Check permissions, never role names. Super Admin holds the full catalogue explicitly ÔÇö no `Gate::before`.

## 8. Identity stripping (DOC-04)

Without `view-worker-identity`, strip at every serialization boundary (JsonResource, Inertia props, Reverb, exports, public pages, reports).

